    "body": "### Problem\n\nI would like to  contribute to C code (https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/32616) but I have an issue with uncrustify:\n\n```\nâžœ make lint\n[  0%] Performing install step for 'uncrustify'\n[  0%] Generating version header\n-- Unable to determine version from source tree; fallback version '0.80.1_f' will be used\n-- (This is normal if you are building from a zip / tarball)\n[  0%] Built target generate_version_header\n[100%] Built target uncrustify\nInstall the project...\n-- Install configuration: \"Release\"\nCMake Error at cmake_install.cmake:52 (file):\n  file INSTALL cannot find \"/home/teto/neovim/build/usr/bin/uncrustify\": No\n  such file or directory.\n```\n\nthe errors at cmake_install.cmake:52\n ```\nif(NOT DEFINED CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX)\n  set(CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX \"/home/teto/neovim/build/usr\")\nendif()\nstring(REGEX REPLACE \"/$\" \"\" CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX \"${CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX}\")\n\n...\n\n  file(INSTALL DESTINATION \"${CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX}/bin\" TYPE EXECUTABLE FILES \"/home/teto/neovim/build/usr/bin/uncrustify\")   # <<- here\n```\nThe file /home/teto/neovim/build/usr/bin/uncrustify doesn't exist which seems to trigger the error ? also it might be  a bit tautological as if CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX and I understand correctly it seems to install the file to its existing location ? I tried to find for an uncrustify executable but seems like the linking never completed ? (tried `fd -uL uncrustify` ) would like to log the commands at cmake_install.cmake.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nthis happens in a nix shell.\n```\n$ nix develop github:nix-community/neovim-nightly-overlay\n$ rm -rf build CMakeCache.txt\n$ cmakeConfigurePhase # calls cmake with some nix settings\n$ make\n```\ndundargoc already gave it a spin and it was fine on darwin ? just not fine on linux.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI am ok with a hack like providing my own uncrustiy (nixpkgs provides one) but I suspect the whole deps thing is intertwined in the build system and I am not sure I can skip those. How would I call uncrustify bypassing the Makefile ?\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nmaster\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nnope\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nnixos unstable\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nkitty\n\n### Installation\n\nnixpkgs",
