            "body": "I think nix is a godsend for developer but I understand it's not straightforward considering the learning curve :'(\nTurns out this cmake directive:\n ```\n    file(RPATH_CHECK\n         FILE \"$ENV{DESTDIR}${CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX}/bin/uncrustify\"\n         RPATH \"\")\n```\ndeletes the file (confirmed by https://stackoverflow.com/questions/69881222/why-rpath-check-in-cmake-deletes-executable). If I comment it, everything works.\nI am not sure where the RPATH_CHECK comes from. Is it generated by cmake ? nix messes with rpath so that could explain it.\nNot sure how to fix it: ideally the RPATH check could be configured/disabled.",
